WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.733
Hi everyone!

00:00:00.733 --> 00:00:01.399
 

00:00:01.399 --> 00:00:02.999
Today we're going to talk about

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:05.133
a term you've probably heard more frequently

00:00:05.133 --> 00:00:05.766
that is

00:00:05.766 --> 00:00:06.833
sanctions .

00:00:08.233 --> 00:00:09.399
We'll examine sanctions imposed on five of

00:00:09.399 --> 00:00:10.166
the most distinctive,

00:00:10.166 --> 00:00:11.166
influential,

00:00:11.166 --> 00:00:12.866
and well-known countries

00:00:12.866 --> 00:00:14.600
understand what they are all about

00:00:14.600 --> 00:00:16.733
At the same time, we'll also explore

00:00:16.733 --> 00:00:18.533
the underlying logic of sanctions,

00:00:19.166 --> 00:00:20.166
their methods, 

00:00:20.166 --> 00:00:22.133
how the sanctioned countries can retaliate,

00:00:22.133 --> 00:00:22.866
and most importantly, whether

00:00:22.866 --> 00:00:24.933
these sanctions are actually effective.

00:00:27.433 --> 00:00:28.833
First, let me test your knowledge

00:00:28.833 --> 00:00:30.066
Do you know which country has been 

00:00:30.066 --> 00:00:32.599
under continuous sanctions for the longest period since World War II ? 

00:00:33.199 --> 00:00:34.766
It's Cuba! 

00:00:36.500 --> 00:00:38.633
In 1959, Castro's revolution

00:00:38.633 --> 00:00:40.433
overthrew the pro-American Batista government.

00:00:40.433 --> 00:00:41.866
Cuba embarked on the socialist path,

00:00:41.866 --> 00:00:42.866
adopted a planned economy,

00:00:42.866 --> 00:00:44.200
and became very close to the Soviet Union.

00:00:44.899 --> 00:00:47.899
In 1962, the world was shaken by the outbreak of the Cuban Missile Crisis.

00:00:47.899 --> 00:00:49.066
US and the Soviet Union confront each other in Cuba,

00:00:49.066 --> 00:00:50.899
nearly triggering World War III.

00:00:50.899 --> 00:00:53.033
Ultimately, the Soviet Union agreed to remove the Cuban Missiles

00:00:53.033 --> 00:00:54.633
and the US pledged not to invade Cuba.

00:00:54.633 --> 00:00:55.766
While this averted a hot war

00:00:55.766 --> 00:00:57.799
the US immediately played its first

00:00:57.800 --> 00:00:59.500
high-intensity card

00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:00.299
economic sanctions

00:01:01.566 --> 00:01:03.266
Actually before Castro was in power

00:01:03.266 --> 00:01:05.066
the US had already begun sanctioning Cuba

00:01:05.066 --> 00:01:06.699
prohibiting oil exports

00:01:06.699 --> 00:01:08.266
and reducing sugar import quotas.

00:01:08.266 --> 00:01:09.666
However, after the 1962 missile crisis,

00:01:09.666 --> 00:01:10.633
the intensity of these sanctions

00:01:10.633 --> 00:01:12.266
increased by several orders of magnitude.

00:01:12.266 --> 00:01:13.766
In 1963, Kennedy issued

00:01:13.766 --> 00:01:15.766
the Cuban Assets Control Act, a

00:01:15.766 --> 00:01:17.966
comprehensive ban on all Cuban imports

00:01:17.966 --> 00:01:19.566
and strict restrictions on exports,

00:01:19.566 --> 00:01:22.199
thus initiating a complete trade blockade against Cuba.

00:01:22.966 --> 00:01:24.699
These sanctions were quickly escalated

00:01:24.699 --> 00:01:26.566
they froze Cuban assets in the United States.

00:01:26.566 --> 00:01:28.499
Those Cuban companies in the US were told to

00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:29.099
shut down

00:01:29.100 --> 00:01:30.266
their earnings

00:01:30.266 --> 00:01:31.666
and savings in the US were frozen

00:01:32.800 --> 00:01:34.566
This is essentially the two most 

00:01:34.566 --> 00:01:35.866
classic forms of economic sanctions : 

00:01:35.866 --> 00:01:37.699
trade blockade and asset freezing.

00:01:37.699 --> 00:01:39.366
A trade blockade means I won't buy from you,

00:01:39.366 --> 00:01:40.199
preventing you from making money

00:01:40.199 --> 00:01:41.566
and I also won't sell to you,

00:01:41.566 --> 00:01:42.633
causing shortages.

00:01:42.633 --> 00:01:43.433
Asset freezing

00:01:43.433 --> 00:01:44.899
means freezing all of

00:01:44.899 --> 00:01:45.966
your country's government assets

00:01:45.966 --> 00:01:46.866
within my territory.

00:01:46.866 --> 00:01:47.833
Even if you want to withdraw

00:01:47.833 --> 00:01:49.066
or do business with others,

00:01:49.066 --> 00:01:49.666
you can't.

00:01:49.666 --> 00:01:51.100
So, how effective are

00:01:51.100 --> 00:01:52.466
these harsh sanctions?

00:01:52.500 --> 00:01:53.066
The answer is

00:01:53.066 --> 00:01:54.066
not so good .

00:01:54.066 --> 00:01:54.966
After 1963, Cuba's

00:01:54.966 --> 00:01:57.066
economy and foreign trade

00:01:57.066 --> 00:01:58.233
continued to grow.

00:01:58.233 --> 00:01:59.033
Why?

00:01:59.066 --> 00:02:00.433
Because it had a powerful backer

00:02:00.433 --> 00:02:01.233
Soviet Union

00:02:01.800 --> 00:02:04.066
The Soviet Union and several socialist countries in Eastern Europe

00:02:04.066 --> 00:02:06.299
accounted for three-quarters of Cuba’s foreign trade.

00:02:06.300 --> 00:02:07.899
They not only being Cuba's largest export market

00:02:07.899 --> 00:02:09.433
but also providing Cuba with substantial

00:02:09.433 --> 00:02:11.633
material and energy subsidies,

00:02:12.066 --> 00:02:13.333
especially sugar

00:02:13.333 --> 00:02:15.799
At the time, the Soviet Union would import Cuban sugar

00:02:15.800 --> 00:02:16.666
at six times the market price

00:02:16.666 --> 00:02:18.466
basically, giving money away.

00:02:18.466 --> 00:02:20.966
With such strong strategic support,

00:02:20.966 --> 00:02:22.799
even under the very nose of the United States,

00:02:22.800 --> 00:02:24.199
the US couldn't do much about it.

00:02:24.199 --> 00:02:26.466
However, after the collapse of the Soviet Union, things changed.

00:02:26.766 --> 00:02:28.433
Cuba's backers disappeared overnight

00:02:28.433 --> 00:02:30.866
and it experienced the most severe economic crisis in its history.

00:02:30.866 --> 00:02:32.000
From 1990 to 1993,

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:34.166
its GDP shrank by about one-third,

00:02:34.166 --> 00:02:35.966
foreign trade declined by 60%, there was

00:02:35.966 --> 00:02:37.033
a severe shortage of goods,

00:02:37.033 --> 00:02:39.566
many areas experienced power outages for 8 to 16 hours a day,

00:02:39.566 --> 00:02:41.366
and food supplies were strictly limited

00:02:42.233 --> 00:02:43.166
How limited was it

00:02:43.166 --> 00:02:45.133
The average adult weight in Cuba

00:02:45.133 --> 00:02:46.633
dropped by 5-10 kilograms.

00:02:46.633 --> 00:02:47.266
You can imagine

00:02:47.266 --> 00:02:49.666
how bad that period was for the Cuban economy.

00:02:49.666 --> 00:02:50.866
There's a specific term in economics

00:02:50.866 --> 00:02:52.100
called "special period,"

00:02:52.100 --> 00:02:53.933
it wasn't called Cuba 's special period

00:02:53.933 --> 00:02:55.066
just special period

00:02:55.066 --> 00:02:56.266
You can see how special it was.

00:02:56.266 --> 00:02:58.199
However, despite such a huge impact,

00:02:58.199 --> 00:02:59.433
Cuba recovered quickly.

00:02:59.433 --> 00:03:00.899
This special period lasted less than five years.

00:03:00.899 --> 00:03:02.066
Especially after 2000

00:03:02.066 --> 00:03:03.833
look at how rapidly Cuba's GDP grew!

00:03:03.833 --> 00:03:04.566
Why?

00:03:04.566 --> 00:03:06.366
Did the US ease sanctions?

00:03:06.366 --> 00:03:07.266
Actually, no,

00:03:07.266 --> 00:03:08.433
it might have even intensified.

00:03:08.433 --> 00:03:09.100
They just made it through

00:03:09.100 --> 00:03:10.500
Its recovery was due to economic reforms,

00:03:10.500 --> 00:03:12.033
such as the rapid development of tourism,

00:03:12.033 --> 00:03:13.833
but there was also a very crucial point

00:03:13.833 --> 00:03:15.999
it solved a very, very core problem

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:16.866
energy.

00:03:18.399 --> 00:03:19.433
Cuba previously relied heavily

00:03:19.433 --> 00:03:20.366
on the Soviet Union for energy

00:03:20.366 --> 00:03:21.399
but after the collapse of the Soviet Union,

00:03:21.399 --> 00:03:23.799
Russia's attitude towards Cuba became very cold.

00:03:23.800 --> 00:03:25.366
So, Cuba sought

00:03:25.366 --> 00:03:26.366
a new ally

00:03:26.366 --> 00:03:27.300
and right in front of it

00:03:27.300 --> 00:03:28.433
was a major oil producer

00:03:28.433 --> 00:03:29.000
that is

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:30.166
Venezuela

00:03:30.233 --> 00:03:31.433
Venezuela too

00:03:31.433 --> 00:03:33.300
was later embroiled in sanctions, which

00:03:33.300 --> 00:03:33.899
we'll discuss later.

00:03:33.899 --> 00:03:35.233
However, since the 1990s, 

00:03:35.233 --> 00:03:36.600
it has maintained a very close relationship with Cuba.

00:03:36.600 --> 00:03:38.800
Venezuelan President Hugo Chávez and Fidel Castro

00:03:38.800 --> 00:03:40.199
had a very good personal relationship.

00:03:40.199 --> 00:03:42.233
Chávez often said that Castro

00:03:42.233 --> 00:03:43.433
was his mentor,

00:03:43.466 --> 00:03:45.366
and he even

00:03:45.366 --> 00:03:45.933
flew to Cuba specifically

00:03:45.933 --> 00:03:47.600
to attend Castro's birthday party as a surprise. 

00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:48.300
In short, Venezuela

00:03:48.300 --> 00:03:50.899
not only helped Cuba through its most difficult period

00:03:50.899 --> 00:03:52.033
but also arguably

00:03:52.033 --> 00:03:54.033
revitalized Cuba's economy.

00:03:55.100 --> 00:03:57.066
Actually, relations between the US and Cuba

00:03:57.066 --> 00:03:58.433
haven't always been so tense.

00:03:58.433 --> 00:04:00.266
In 2009, during Obama's presidency,

00:04:00.266 --> 00:04:02.866
there was a period of thawing between Cuba and the US,

00:04:02.866 --> 00:04:04.766
and the two countries even established diplomatic relations in 2015.

00:04:04.766 --> 00:04:06.633
But then Trump took office,

00:04:06.633 --> 00:04:08.633
and Obama's promises no longer held true.

00:04:08.633 --> 00:04:10.399
Cuba was subject to sanctions again

00:04:10.399 --> 00:04:11.633
and it was relisted as

00:04:11.633 --> 00:04:13.399
a state sponsor of terrorism,

00:04:13.399 --> 00:04:14.966
with over 200 additional sanctions imposed.

00:04:14.966 --> 00:04:18.966
The US will not lift sanctions against Cuba

00:04:18.966 --> 00:04:21.866
unless it grants the Cuban people

00:04:21.866 --> 00:04:23.333
complete political freedom .

00:04:24.266 --> 00:04:26.033
This year, Trump signed a memorandum

00:04:26.033 --> 00:04:26.766
to further tighten 

00:04:26.766 --> 00:04:28.466
sanctions against Cuba

00:04:28.466 --> 00:04:30.666
and the US has returned to a pattern of extreme sanctions 

00:04:30.666 --> 00:04:31.733
and embargoes against Cuba.

00:04:31.733 --> 00:04:32.199
I suspect

00:04:32.199 --> 00:04:34.233
many people, influenced by media reports,

00:04:34.233 --> 00:04:36.800
feel that Cuba is a poor and underdeveloped country.

00:04:36.800 --> 00:04:38.833
It does face humanitarian problems

00:04:38.833 --> 00:04:40.166
due to US restrictions on supplies

00:04:40.166 --> 00:04:41.100
making it difficult to buy iPhones

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:42.100
and even access McDonald's.

00:04:42.100 --> 00:04:43.399
However, if you look at its GDP growth, as

00:04:43.399 --> 00:04:44.266
we just saw,

00:04:44.266 --> 00:04:45.499
the curve is astonishing.

00:04:45.500 --> 00:04:46.933
In 2020, its per capita GDP

00:04:46.933 --> 00:04:48.100
approached $10,000,

00:04:48.100 --> 00:04:49.033
surpassing Mexico

00:04:49.033 --> 00:04:50.133
and more than double that of Vietnam.

00:04:50.133 --> 00:04:50.600
Overall,

00:04:50.600 --> 00:04:52.800
its economic growth rate is quite good,

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:54.500
seemingly unaffected by the sanctions.

00:04:54.500 --> 00:04:55.299
Why?

00:04:55.500 --> 00:04:56.799
Well, it's easy to understand.

00:04:56.800 --> 00:04:57.933
Besides the US,

00:04:57.933 --> 00:04:58.666
no other countries

00:04:58.666 --> 00:05:00.500
have imposed sanctions on Cuba. 

00:05:00.500 --> 00:05:01.366
In fact,

00:05:01.366 --> 00:05:01.899
most countries

00:05:01.899 --> 00:05:03.066
strongly oppose

00:05:03.066 --> 00:05:04.566
the excessive US sanctions against Cuba.

00:05:04.566 --> 00:05:05.733
For example, in 2024,

00:05:05.733 --> 00:05:06.966
the UN passed a resolution

00:05:06.966 --> 00:05:09.233
to end US sanctions against Cuba's economy

00:05:09.233 --> 00:05:10.466
commercial and financial blockade

00:05:10.466 --> 00:05:11.433
A voting was held on this

00:05:11.433 --> 00:05:13.466
resulted in 187 votes in favour,

00:05:13.466 --> 00:05:15.233
2 against (US and Israel)

00:05:15.233 --> 00:05:16.033
and 1 abstention

00:05:16.033 --> 00:05:16.699
from Moldova.

00:05:16.699 --> 00:05:17.466
This resolution,

00:05:17.466 --> 00:05:18.766
originating from the UN General Assembly,

00:05:18.766 --> 00:05:19.833
is not legally binding ; 

00:05:19.833 --> 00:05:20.599
it's merely a recommendation.

00:05:20.600 --> 00:05:21.300
However, you can see that

00:05:21.300 --> 00:05:23.100
most countries' stance is very clear:

00:05:23.100 --> 00:05:23.566
this

00:05:23.566 --> 00:05:25.633
is purely humanitarian oppression,

00:05:25.633 --> 00:05:27.566
and Cuba hasn't done anything particularly heinous,

00:05:27.566 --> 00:05:28.799
This is a bit unfair.

00:05:28.800 --> 00:05:30.366
Anyway, that's the gist of it.

00:05:30.366 --> 00:05:30.866
Currently,

00:05:30.866 --> 00:05:33.399
Cuba has very close trading partners

00:05:33.399 --> 00:05:34.699
with Venezuela, the EU, China, and others,

00:05:34.699 --> 00:05:36.466
but there's still a significant trade deficit.

00:05:36.466 --> 00:05:38.233
Trade channels aren't very smooth, and

00:05:38.233 --> 00:05:39.766
in the last two years, Cuba has been mired in an economic crisis

00:05:39.766 --> 00:05:41.399
We'll discuss this in detail

00:05:41.399 --> 00:05:42.433
if we have a chance to talk about Cuba on its own.

00:05:43.766 --> 00:05:45.633
What exactly are economic sanctions?

00:05:45.633 --> 00:05:47.233
They are a form of coercion that

00:05:47.233 --> 00:05:49.300
attempts to force an actor to change their behavior by

00:05:49.300 --> 00:05:51.966
disrupting economic exchanges.

00:05:51.966 --> 00:05:53.399
Simply put, it's about making things difficult,

00:05:53.399 --> 00:05:54.066
causing annoyance,

00:05:54.066 --> 00:05:55.033
and inflicting pain

00:05:55.033 --> 00:05:56.266
forcing you to compromise

00:05:56.266 --> 00:05:56.999
and make concessions

00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:57.799
Economic sanctions

00:05:57.800 --> 00:05:58.966
are generally not an end in themselves,

00:05:58.966 --> 00:05:59.999
but rather a means

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:02.100
to deter the other party and achieve certain goals

00:06:02.100 --> 00:06:03.233
Common goals include

00:06:03.233 --> 00:06:04.466
policy changes,

00:06:04.466 --> 00:06:05.466
regime change,

00:06:05.466 --> 00:06:06.366
eliminating terrorism,

00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:07.100
ending wars

00:06:07.100 --> 00:06:08.833
human rights, democracy, and so on.

00:06:08.833 --> 00:06:09.966
In the Cuban case,

00:06:09.966 --> 00:06:11.766
although the US appears to have many goals

00:06:11.766 --> 00:06:12.999
the most fundamental and core one

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:14.466
is regime change.

00:06:14.466 --> 00:06:15.499
From this perspective,

00:06:15.500 --> 00:06:17.500
the US sanctions against Cuba are certainly unsuccessful.

00:06:17.500 --> 00:06:18.366
In fact, historically,

00:06:18.366 --> 00:06:20.133
the percentage of sanctions that actually achieve their objectives

00:06:20.133 --> 00:06:21.033
is very low,

00:06:21.033 --> 00:06:22.199
less than 10%

00:06:22.199 --> 00:06:23.233
But there are successful examples

00:06:23.233 --> 00:06:25.300
A typical one is South Africa.

00:06:25.300 --> 00:06:26.899
From 1948, it

00:06:26.899 --> 00:06:28.066
implemented apartheid, with

00:06:28.066 --> 00:06:28.999
a minority of whites

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:31.000
ruling over the majority of blacks and people of colour.

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:32.033
Later, in the 1980s,

00:06:32.033 --> 00:06:33.966
almost all countries in the world unified

00:06:33.966 --> 00:06:35.299
in imposing economic sanctions on South Africa

00:06:35.300 --> 00:06:36.066
cutting off its trade

00:06:36.066 --> 00:06:37.066
and aid.

00:06:37.066 --> 00:06:39.300
You have to understand that South Africa was heavily reliant on its gold and

00:06:39.300 --> 00:06:40.100
mineral exports,

00:06:40.100 --> 00:06:41.300
so this blow was very powerful.

00:06:41.300 --> 00:06:43.033
Coupled with external public opinion pressure and

00:06:43.033 --> 00:06:44.100
internal resistance movements,

00:06:44.100 --> 00:06:45.266
it successfully forced the South African government

00:06:45.266 --> 00:06:46.766
to release Mandela in 1990,

00:06:46.766 --> 00:06:48.433
gradually abolishing apartheid.

00:06:48.433 --> 00:06:50.733
Then the West slowly eased its sanctions.

00:06:51.033 --> 00:06:52.166
This is a very successful example.

00:06:52.166 --> 00:06:52.766
You see,

00:06:52.766 --> 00:06:54.299
the main difference between South Africa and Cuba

00:06:54.300 --> 00:06:56.533
is that other countries pulled in.

00:06:56.533 --> 00:06:58.066
The effect of sanctions greatly amplifies

00:06:58.066 --> 00:07:00.899
However, even with global cooperation,

00:07:00.899 --> 00:07:02.099
some countries can withstand the pressure.

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:03.899
Even the US, which only intends to sanction

00:07:03.899 --> 00:07:04.866
one country, has its own

00:07:04.899 --> 00:07:05.699
methods.

00:07:05.699 --> 00:07:06.466
But wait,

00:07:06.466 --> 00:07:07.733
we'll see soon enough.

00:07:09.133 --> 00:07:09.833
Cuba

00:07:09.833 --> 00:07:10.733
has been sanctioned for years, and

00:07:10.733 --> 00:07:11.866
its economy is actually still relatively stable.

00:07:11.866 --> 00:07:13.666
But its close ally,

00:07:13.666 --> 00:07:14.433
Venezuela,

00:07:14.433 --> 00:07:15.399
After being sanctioned

00:07:15.399 --> 00:07:16.933
has become one of the worst-performing 

00:07:16.933 --> 00:07:18.600
economies in the world

00:07:18.600 --> 00:07:19.633
Venezuela has the world's

00:07:19.633 --> 00:07:21.266
largest proven oil reserves,

00:07:21.266 --> 00:07:22.066
and should

00:07:22.066 --> 00:07:22.833
theoretically be

00:07:22.833 --> 00:07:23.833
one of the richest countries in

00:07:23.833 --> 00:07:25.033
the 20th century.

00:07:25.033 --> 00:07:26.233
Instead, it's in complete chaos.

00:07:26.233 --> 00:07:27.800
Let's talk about what happened in Venezuela.

00:07:29.133 --> 00:07:32.099
In 2005, the US began sanctions against Venezuela.

00:07:32.100 --> 00:07:34.066
Initially, the sanctions imposed on Venezuela were not very broad

00:07:34.066 --> 00:07:34.833
Mostly about

00:07:35.100 --> 00:07:36.600
widespread drug abuse

00:07:36.600 --> 00:07:37.600
combating terrorism

00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:38.899
poor cooperation

00:07:38.899 --> 00:07:40.499
Individuals were being targeted

00:07:40.500 --> 00:07:41.433
including government officials

00:07:41.433 --> 00:07:42.600
adding up to dozens of people

00:07:42.600 --> 00:07:43.633
and sanction was imposed

00:07:44.600 --> 00:07:45.100
Later,

00:07:45.100 --> 00:07:47.000
due to Venezuela's dire economic situation and

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:48.199
severe inflation,

00:07:48.199 --> 00:07:49.099
the public could no longer tolerate

00:07:49.100 --> 00:07:51.899
leading to nearly ten thousand

00:07:51.899 --> 00:07:53.499
nationwide protests in 2014.

00:07:53.500 --> 00:07:54.433
Maduro

00:07:55.033 --> 00:07:56.833
responded with a strong crackdown

00:07:56.833 --> 00:07:58.799
on these protests,

00:07:59.633 --> 00:08:00.866
which the United States deemed

00:08:00.866 --> 00:08:01.333
 

00:08:01.333 --> 00:08:03.466
a human rights violation by the Venezuelan government.

00:08:03.466 --> 00:08:04.699
This prompted the US to impose sanctions and pressure,

00:08:04.699 --> 00:08:05.733
and Obama signed

00:08:05.733 --> 00:08:08.866
the "Venezuela Human Rights and Civil Society Protection Act of 2014"

00:08:08.866 --> 00:08:11.133
began imposing sanctions on more government officials

00:08:11.133 --> 00:08:11.999
 and official entities

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:12.600
but so far

00:08:12.600 --> 00:08:14.666
it has remained a targeted attack on individuals.

00:08:14.666 --> 00:08:15.500
As we mentioned earlier,

00:08:15.500 --> 00:08:16.233
sanction methods

00:08:16.233 --> 00:08:18.033
typically include trade sanctions and asset freezes,

00:08:18.033 --> 00:08:20.199
which are already quite severe.

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:20.833
However sanctions

00:08:20.833 --> 00:08:22.633
usually don't start so severely;

00:08:22.633 --> 00:08:25.099
they usually begin with certain individuals, entities, or

00:08:25.100 --> 00:08:26.299
companies. 

00:08:26.299 --> 00:08:28.066
This may not have a significant impact

00:08:28.066 --> 00:08:28.966
on reversing the overall situation

00:08:28.966 --> 00:08:30.133
it only targets those individuals.

00:08:30.133 --> 00:08:31.599
And these targeted individuals

00:08:31.600 --> 00:08:33.600
are usually very powerful domestically, making

00:08:33.600 --> 00:08:34.633
them difficult to target.

00:08:34.633 --> 00:08:36.466
Therefore, it becomes symbolic,

00:08:36.466 --> 00:08:37.799
expressing a tough stance,

00:08:37.799 --> 00:08:39.266
as if to say, "Don't let me catch you,

00:08:39.266 --> 00:08:40.099
or else

00:08:40.100 --> 00:08:41.166
you’ll pay for it"

00:08:43.033 --> 00:08:43.933
In 2014,

00:08:43.966 --> 00:08:44.933
the sanctions imposed on Venezuela

00:08:44.933 --> 00:08:45.833
weren't just imposed by the US,

00:08:45.833 --> 00:08:48.033
 Canada, the EU, the UK, joined in

00:08:48.033 --> 00:08:49.233
but they were relatively restrained,

00:08:49.233 --> 00:08:51.533
targeting individuals or certain weapons.

00:08:51.533 --> 00:08:54.033
But then came

00:08:54.033 --> 00:08:54.699
Trump.

00:08:54.700 --> 00:08:56.600
At the start of his first term, he began to exert pressure.

00:08:56.600 --> 00:08:57.233
In 2017,

00:08:57.233 --> 00:08:59.266
the US began imposing sanctions

00:08:59.266 --> 00:08:59.833
on Venezuela at the national level,

00:08:59.833 --> 00:09:01.633
prohibiting its bonds from trading in the US market

00:09:01.633 --> 00:09:03.599
essentially preventing it from accessing the US financial market.

00:09:03.600 --> 00:09:05.233
Some might think this sounds alright

00:09:05.233 --> 00:09:07.066
It's just preventing it from financing in the US, right?

00:09:07.066 --> 00:09:07.500
But let me tell you,

00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:09.500
this is actually extremely detrimental to Venezuela.

00:09:09.500 --> 00:09:12.133
The US essentially orchestrated a precise strike.

00:09:12.133 --> 00:09:12.933
On who?

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:16.400
It's Venezuela's state-owned oil company, PDVSA.

00:09:17.733 --> 00:09:19.333
We all know that fossil fuels

00:09:19.333 --> 00:09:20.399
like oil and natural gas

00:09:20.399 --> 00:09:21.933
are crucial for countries

00:09:21.933 --> 00:09:22.666
that rely heavily on them.

00:09:22.666 --> 00:09:24.099
Such as Iran and Russia.

00:09:24.100 --> 00:09:25.500
However, oil is even more important for Venezuela

00:09:25.500 --> 00:09:27.466
especially to the government

00:09:27.466 --> 00:09:28.333
It's more important

00:09:30.066 --> 00:09:31.866
because Venezuela's economy is in dire straits.

00:09:31.866 --> 00:09:33.799
Government revenue comes almost entirely from oil.

00:09:33.799 --> 00:09:34.899
While Iran and Russia

00:09:34.899 --> 00:09:36.699
at least have relatively well-established economic frameworks

00:09:36.700 --> 00:09:38.233
whether above-ground or underground,

00:09:38.233 --> 00:09:39.299
whatever their structure—

00:09:39.299 --> 00:09:41.666
they have their own set of operating rules.

00:09:41.666 --> 00:09:43.633
But Venezuela's economy

00:09:43.633 --> 00:09:46.066
aside from oil, is essentially a disorganized mess.

00:09:46.066 --> 00:09:47.466
It has such a significant weakness that

00:09:47.466 --> 00:09:48.899
the US naturally targeted it,

00:09:48.899 --> 00:09:50.266
starting with financial sanctions,

00:09:50.266 --> 00:09:51.199
because its oil companies

00:09:51.200 --> 00:09:53.100
were previously heavily reliant on the US financial market.

00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:53.833
The company seeking financing

00:09:53.833 --> 00:09:54.799
was excluded, its cash flow

00:09:54.799 --> 00:09:56.233
was immediately disrupted,

00:09:56.233 --> 00:09:57.200
and its external trade activities

00:09:57.200 --> 00:09:58.600
became virtually impossible.

00:09:58.633 --> 00:09:59.666
Later, in 2019,

00:09:59.666 --> 00:10:00.633
the US

00:10:00.633 --> 00:10:02.033
imposed further sanctions

00:10:02.033 --> 00:10:03.299
on the Venezuelan oil company,

00:10:03.299 --> 00:10:04.199
such as blocking payments

00:10:04.200 --> 00:10:05.000
and freezing assets

00:10:06.066 --> 00:10:07.700
As a sanctioned country,

00:10:07.700 --> 00:10:09.833
its usual countermeasures are not hard to imagine

00:10:09.833 --> 00:10:11.299
it quickly seeks other buyers,

00:10:11.299 --> 00:10:12.533
finding alternative buyers

00:10:12.533 --> 00:10:14.066
With such a scarce resource as oil, if

00:10:14.133 --> 00:10:14.833
the US sanctions me,

00:10:14.833 --> 00:10:15.533
Europe sanctions me—

00:10:15.533 --> 00:10:16.399
there will always be someone who needs it.

00:10:16.399 --> 00:10:17.266
Even if it's a bit troublesome

00:10:17.266 --> 00:10:18.266
but in most cases,

00:10:18.266 --> 00:10:19.899
alternative buyers can be found;

00:10:19.899 --> 00:10:21.133
it won't be completely blocked.

00:10:21.133 --> 00:10:22.699
You see, after Venezuela was sanctioned,

00:10:22.700 --> 00:10:23.466
President Maduro

00:10:23.466 --> 00:10:25.466
immediately moved the oil company's European office 

00:10:25.466 --> 00:10:27.266
from Lisbon to Moscow

00:10:27.266 --> 00:10:29.199
and began to sell a large amount of crude oil to Russia,

00:10:29.200 --> 00:10:31.100
which then resells it to other countries

00:10:31.100 --> 00:10:33.333
primarily India.

00:10:33.333 --> 00:10:33.866
However,

00:10:33.866 --> 00:10:35.833
these alternative solutions are more expensive

00:10:35.833 --> 00:10:36.866
and have limited demand.

00:10:36.866 --> 00:10:37.899
Therefore, after the sanctions,

00:10:37.899 --> 00:10:39.833
Venezuela's oil revenue plummeted,

00:10:39.833 --> 00:10:41.466
with government revenue as a percentage of GDP

00:10:41.466 --> 00:10:42.666
falling from around 30%

00:10:42.666 --> 00:10:43.933
to less than 10%.

00:10:43.933 --> 00:10:46.066
Simultaneously, its financing channels were blocked by the US.

00:10:46.066 --> 00:10:46.833
Imagine if your

00:10:46.833 --> 00:10:48.433
income were cut by a third,

00:10:48.433 --> 00:10:49.399
and loans were restricted

00:10:49.399 --> 00:10:51.299
small loans, consumer loans, all were off-limits—

00:10:51.299 --> 00:10:53.499
you'd definitely cut all unnecessary expenses.

00:10:53.500 --> 00:10:54.666
If a chair leg breaks,

00:10:54.666 --> 00:10:56.033
you'll prop it up with stones;

00:10:56.033 --> 00:10:56.833
if you catch a cold

00:10:56.833 --> 00:10:57.833
you'll bear it ;

00:10:57.833 --> 00:10:58.899
if a light bulb burns out

00:10:58.899 --> 00:10:59.699
you'll go to bed early

00:10:59.700 --> 00:11:00.633
if the toilet breaks

00:11:00.633 --> 00:11:01.799
you'll use a public restroom.

00:11:01.799 --> 00:11:02.899
Venezuela is pretty much the same

00:11:02.899 --> 00:11:05.333
They began drastically cutting spending on

00:11:05.333 --> 00:11:06.600
basic necessities and infrastructure maintenance,

00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:09.100
leading to severe aging of many infrastructure projects,

00:11:09.100 --> 00:11:10.000
frequent power outages, and

00:11:10.933 --> 00:11:13.499
difficulties maintaining the water, sanitation, and healthcare systems.

00:11:13.500 --> 00:11:15.066
Venezuela's economy completely collapsed,

00:11:15.066 --> 00:11:18.933
with inflation exceeding 300,000 percent in 2019.

00:11:20.233 --> 00:11:22.633
Recently, relations between the US and Venezuela have become even more tense.

00:11:22.633 --> 00:11:23.833
The US, citing "drugs,"

00:11:23.833 --> 00:11:25.633
has bombed several Venezuelan ships.

00:11:25.633 --> 00:11:27.733
The State Department and the Department of Justice have also offered a $50 million

00:11:27.733 --> 00:11:28.833
reward for information

00:11:28.833 --> 00:11:30.733
leading to the arrest or conviction of Maduro

00:11:30.733 --> 00:11:32.100
The official reasons

00:11:32.100 --> 00:11:33.233
given by the US for targeting Maduro

00:11:33.233 --> 00:11:34.700
are twofold: his alleged involvement in drugs

00:11:34.700 --> 00:11:36.033
and his alleged suppression of democracy.

00:11:36.100 --> 00:11:37.133
However, in all fairness, given

00:11:37.133 --> 00:11:38.033
his dire economic situation,

00:11:38.033 --> 00:11:39.099
we cannot solely blame sanctions,

00:11:39.100 --> 00:11:40.266
 and even sanctions alone 

00:11:40.266 --> 00:11:41.433
cannot address this issue. 

00:11:41.433 --> 00:11:43.266
We definitely won't go into detail about that today

00:11:43.266 --> 00:11:43.700
To be honest,

00:11:43.700 --> 00:11:45.299
the countries we've talked about today

00:11:45.299 --> 00:11:46.299
are all very interesting

00:11:46.299 --> 00:11:47.433
even quite bizarre.

00:11:47.433 --> 00:11:49.666
We'll dedicate a separate episode to them if we have the chance.

00:11:49.666 --> 00:11:50.199
But today,

00:11:50.200 --> 00:11:52.400
our focus is still on sanctions.

00:11:52.899 --> 00:11:54.233
After entering hyperinflation,

00:11:54.233 --> 00:11:55.533
for ordinary people,

00:11:55.533 --> 00:11:56.933
water and electricity outages are commonplace.

00:11:56.933 --> 00:11:59.066
The banknotes are so hot to hold

00:11:59.066 --> 00:12:01.133
that they feel like they need to queue for a whole day to buy food.

00:12:01.133 --> 00:12:02.799
But even though the situation is already so bad,

00:12:02.799 --> 00:12:04.633
it can be said that sanctions have

00:12:04.633 --> 00:12:05.466
pushed Venezuela's economy into an abyss.

00:12:05.466 --> 00:12:06.799
But at least so far,

00:12:06.799 --> 00:12:08.699
the purpose of these sanctions has not been achieved

00:12:08.700 --> 00:12:10.033
Maduro is still the president.

00:12:10.033 --> 00:12:12.133
Look at the examples of Venezuela and Cuba, and

00:12:12.133 --> 00:12:13.866
we have found a very important underlying principle

00:12:13.866 --> 00:12:15.100
is that economic sanctions

00:12:15.100 --> 00:12:16.100
regardless of who they target

00:12:16.100 --> 00:12:18.533
it ultimately directly oppress

00:12:18.533 --> 00:12:21.099
the lives of the lower classes in the sanctioned country.

00:12:22.833 --> 00:12:24.466
The cruel logic behind this

00:12:24.466 --> 00:12:26.266
is the hope that by oppressing the lower classes and

00:12:26.266 --> 00:12:27.133
the masses, they

00:12:27.133 --> 00:12:29.599
can drive internal change within the sanctioned country.

00:12:29.600 --> 00:12:30.266
In fact, both

00:12:30.266 --> 00:12:31.133
the sanctioning

00:12:31.133 --> 00:12:32.899
and sanctioned countries' elites

00:12:32.899 --> 00:12:34.199
are well aware of this

00:12:35.299 --> 00:12:36.699
which is quite ironic, isn't it?

00:12:36.700 --> 00:12:38.600
Because often, the reason for sanctions is that

00:12:38.600 --> 00:12:40.533
the sanctioned country suppresses democracy and

00:12:40.533 --> 00:12:41.333
violates human rights.

00:12:41.399 --> 00:12:42.033
So, how about this:

00:12:42.033 --> 00:12:43.833
I'll further oppress your lives,

00:12:43.833 --> 00:12:45.100
making you even more miserable,

00:12:45.100 --> 00:12:47.200
to increase your determination to resist,

00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:47.833
right? 

00:12:47.833 --> 00:12:49.233
Let's leave it at that.

00:12:49.233 --> 00:12:50.799
We'll look at the next country,

00:12:50.799 --> 00:12:51.566
North Korea.

00:12:52.899 --> 00:12:54.099
The sanctions against North Korea

00:12:54.100 --> 00:12:55.766
mainly revolve around nuclear weapons

00:12:55.766 --> 00:12:56.633
or more precisely, it's about

00:12:56.633 --> 00:12:58.233
weapons of mass destruction.

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:02.100
In 1994, the United States and North Korea reached the Agreed Framework on nuclear issues

00:13:02.100 --> 00:13:03.766
with North Korea agreeing to freeze its nuclear program

00:13:03.766 --> 00:13:05.766
and accept monitoring by the International Atomic Energy Agency

00:13:05.766 --> 00:13:08.299
The US, in turn, provided two light-water reactors

00:13:08.299 --> 00:13:09.133
oil, and

00:13:09.133 --> 00:13:10.599
gradually liberalised its economy.

00:13:10.766 --> 00:13:12.299
However, this agreement didn't last long;

00:13:12.299 --> 00:13:14.533
relations collapsed in 2002,

00:13:14.533 --> 00:13:15.866
with both sides accusing the other of

00:13:15.866 --> 00:13:17.033
failing to fulfill its obligations under the agreement

00:13:17.033 --> 00:13:18.433
We won't go into the details,

00:13:18.433 --> 00:13:19.533
but the agreement broke down,

00:13:19.533 --> 00:13:20.766
and North Korea

00:13:20.766 --> 00:13:22.566
withdrew from the Treaty on the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons in 2003.

00:13:23.933 --> 00:13:24.633
Afterwards,

00:13:24.633 --> 00:13:27.099
China, Japan, North Korea, South Korea, Russia, and the United States

00:13:27.100 --> 00:13:28.166
held multiple rounds of the Six-Party Talks

00:13:28.166 --> 00:13:29.799
regarding the North Korean nuclear issue,

00:13:29.799 --> 00:13:31.433
but it was difficult to reach a substantial agreement.

00:13:36.799 --> 00:13:39.199
In 2006, North Korea conducted its first nuclear test,

00:13:39.200 --> 00:13:40.000
shocking the world. 

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:42.500
The UN Security Council immediately passed Resolution 1718,

00:13:42.500 --> 00:13:44.799
imposing economic, military, and trade sanctions on North Korea.

00:13:44.799 --> 00:13:45.433
In short,

00:13:45.433 --> 00:13:46.166
since then,

00:13:46.166 --> 00:13:47.966
North Korea has continued to conduct nuclear tests,

00:13:47.966 --> 00:13:50.100
and the UN has continuously increased sanctions against it. 

00:13:50.100 --> 00:13:51.799
Every time North Korea conducts a test or launches a missile,

00:13:51.799 --> 00:13:53.299
the UN passes a new sanctions package,

00:13:53.299 --> 00:13:55.133
including personal asset sanctions, financial sanctions,

00:13:55.133 --> 00:13:56.533
and trade sanctions

00:13:56.533 --> 00:13:57.933
at least eight resolutions have been passed

00:13:57.933 --> 00:13:59.266
to expand sanctions against North Korea

00:13:59.266 --> 00:13:59.999
You should know that

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:03.033
the UN rarely imposes sanctions on 

00:14:03.033 --> 00:14:04.433
a country as a whole

00:14:04.433 --> 00:14:05.333
or on its government;

00:14:05.333 --> 00:14:06.899
most of the time it targets individuals

00:14:06.899 --> 00:14:07.766
or entities.

00:14:07.766 --> 00:14:08.166
Why?

00:14:08.166 --> 00:14:09.966
Firstly, imposing sanctions on an entire country

00:14:09.966 --> 00:14:12.166
would be too strong and overwhelming;

00:14:12.166 --> 00:14:12.799
secondly

00:14:12.799 --> 00:14:13.733
the UN Security Council is

00:14:13.733 --> 00:14:14.533
sometimes

00:14:14.533 --> 00:14:16.333
it's difficult to reach a consensus.

00:14:16.333 --> 00:14:17.700
For the UN Security Council

00:14:17.700 --> 00:14:18.933
to pass a sanctions resolution,

00:14:18.933 --> 00:14:21.099
it requires a majority vote of all 15 member states.

00:14:21.100 --> 00:14:21.700
More importantly,

00:14:21.700 --> 00:14:23.899
it's rare for the five permanent members 

00:14:23.899 --> 00:14:24.799
not to veto it.

00:14:24.799 --> 00:14:26.166
For example, in 2022,

00:14:26.166 --> 00:14:28.033
US attempted to push for

00:14:28.033 --> 00:14:29.199
expanded UN sanctions against North Korea

00:14:29.200 --> 00:14:30.933
but this was vetoed by China and Russia. 

00:14:30.933 --> 00:14:31.366
In short,

00:14:31.366 --> 00:14:33.133
UN's numerous rounds of sanctions against North Korea

00:14:33.133 --> 00:14:34.299
are arguably among 

00:14:34.299 --> 00:14:36.633
the most severe globally in terms of scope.

00:14:36.633 --> 00:14:37.366
Yet, North Korea

00:14:37.366 --> 00:14:39.166
continues to act unilaterally.

00:14:39.166 --> 00:14:40.099
You impose your sanctions,

00:14:40.100 --> 00:14:41.000
I'll just keep doing mine.

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:43.099
Look, since 2012, during Kim Jong-un's administration,

00:14:43.100 --> 00:14:45.300
the number of missiles North Korea has launched has increased significantly.

00:14:46.366 --> 00:14:47.000
Isn't that surprising? 

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:48.000
As we just mentioned,

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:50.033
sanctions require the cooperation of many countries.

00:14:50.033 --> 00:14:51.166
Its effect is much stronger

00:14:51.166 --> 00:14:51.966
As for North Korea

00:14:51.966 --> 00:14:53.633
The UN has imposed joint sanctions

00:14:53.633 --> 00:14:55.333
but North Korea hasn't been deterred;

00:14:55.333 --> 00:14:56.700
instead, it has launched more missiles.

00:14:56.700 --> 00:14:57.766
Why is it so defiant?

00:14:57.766 --> 00:14:58.533
Well, on one hand,

00:14:58.533 --> 00:15:00.733
it does indeed have a strong desire for nuclear weapons.

00:15:00.733 --> 00:15:01.866
But a crucial point

00:15:01.866 --> 00:15:03.733
is why sanctions aren't as effective

00:15:03.733 --> 00:15:05.566
North Korea is extremely closed off.

00:15:06.866 --> 00:15:07.666
Since World War II,

00:15:07.666 --> 00:15:08.666
North Korea has been

00:15:08.666 --> 00:15:10.366
one of the world's most closed economies. 

00:15:10.366 --> 00:15:11.866
It was relatively better during the Cold War, but

00:15:11.866 --> 00:15:12.766
after the collapse of the Soviet Union,

00:15:12.766 --> 00:15:13.799
North Korea became even more closed off.

00:15:13.799 --> 00:15:14.166
Think about it:

00:15:14.166 --> 00:15:16.333
the essence of sanctions is to isolate a country

00:15:16.333 --> 00:15:18.399
but North Korea has already isolated itself first.

00:15:18.399 --> 00:15:19.266
Therefore, imposing sanctions

00:15:19.266 --> 00:15:20.633
on it is bound to be less effective.

00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:24.099
In 2017, North Korea's exports as a percentage of GDP

00:15:24.100 --> 00:15:25.700
had been reduced to only 1%.

00:15:25.700 --> 00:15:26.766
You need to know this figure

00:15:26.766 --> 00:15:28.533
countries with rates below 10% are very rare;

00:15:28.533 --> 00:15:30.333
many European countries exceed 40%

00:15:30.333 --> 00:15:33.333
with Singapore and the UAE exceeding 100%,

00:15:33.333 --> 00:15:35.400
while North Korea's is only 1%.

00:15:35.500 --> 00:15:37.599
Actually, North Korea has many ways to circumvent sanctions,

00:15:37.600 --> 00:15:38.533
such as smuggling

00:15:38.533 --> 00:15:39.933
and building its own hacker team

00:15:39.933 --> 00:15:40.799
for money laundering.

00:15:40.799 --> 00:15:41.733
I'll tell you, North Korean hackers

00:15:41.733 --> 00:15:42.500
are quite skilled.

00:15:42.500 --> 00:15:43.399
According to preliminary estimates

00:15:43.399 --> 00:15:44.266
in the past eight years

00:15:44.266 --> 00:15:46.433
they have launched dozens of large-scale cyberattacks

00:15:46.433 --> 00:15:48.066
profiting over $3 billion.

00:15:48.066 --> 00:15:48.733
But regardless,

00:15:48.733 --> 00:15:51.333
North Korea's trade with the outside world is still very limited.

00:15:51.333 --> 00:15:52.100
Speaking of which,

00:15:52.100 --> 00:15:53.033
let me test you.

00:15:53.033 --> 00:15:54.099
Do you know what

00:15:54.100 --> 00:15:55.600
North Korea's main export product,

00:15:55.600 --> 00:15:57.500
accounting for 40% of its exports in 2023, 

00:15:57.500 --> 00:15:59.833
is under the heavy pressure 

00:15:59.866 --> 00:16:00.800
of global sanctions?

00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:02.033
Here are a few options:

00:16:02.033 --> 00:16:03.166
A. Ore

00:16:03.166 --> 00:16:04.333
B. Toys

00:16:04.333 --> 00:16:05.500
C. Automobiles

00:16:05.500 --> 00:16:07.833
D. None of the above

00:16:09.033 --> 00:16:10.599
The answer is

00:16:10.600 --> 00:16:11.833
D. None of the above

00:16:11.833 --> 00:16:12.533
The remaining items are

00:16:12.533 --> 00:16:14.433
also some of North Korea's major exports,

00:16:14.433 --> 00:16:15.499
especially raw ores.

00:16:15.500 --> 00:16:16.733
But its largest export product,

00:16:16.733 --> 00:16:17.833
which I find quite amusing,

00:16:18.433 --> 00:16:19.133
is wigs

00:16:19.266 --> 00:16:21.199
including human hair, beards,

00:16:21.200 --> 00:16:22.066
and false eyelashes.

00:16:22.066 --> 00:16:23.966
In 2023, North Korea exported

00:16:24.033 --> 00:16:26.099
1,680 tons of wigs to China.

00:16:26.100 --> 00:16:26.700
To put that into perspective, 

00:16:26.700 --> 00:16:27.866
I roughly estimated

00:16:27.866 --> 00:16:28.633
that it's equivalent to

00:16:28.633 --> 00:16:31.633
the hair volume of 150 million adult women with long hair.

00:16:31.633 --> 00:16:32.633
North Korea's total population is

00:16:33.200 --> 00:16:35.233
only about 26 million;

00:16:35.233 --> 00:16:36.833
let's assume half of them are women.

00:16:36.833 --> 00:16:38.200
The amount of wigs it exports annually

00:16:38.200 --> 00:16:40.400
is enough to shave all the women in the country ten times over!

00:16:41.533 --> 00:16:42.233
How is that possible?

00:16:42.233 --> 00:16:43.666
Where does it get so many wigs every year?

00:16:43.666 --> 00:16:44.433
Of course, some people

00:16:44.433 --> 00:16:46.433
speculate that it doesn't actually export real human hair.

00:16:46.433 --> 00:16:48.133
That's certainly possible

00:16:48.133 --> 00:16:48.799
but the main reason

00:16:48.799 --> 00:16:50.366
is that it first imports

00:16:50.366 --> 00:16:51.933
"raw hair" from other countries,

00:16:51.933 --> 00:16:52.633
just like with oil.

00:16:52.633 --> 00:16:53.399
You import crude oil

00:16:53.399 --> 00:16:53.966
and then refine it

00:16:53.966 --> 00:16:55.500
For hair, I need to import raw hair.

00:16:55.500 --> 00:16:56.133
For North Korea,

00:16:56.133 --> 00:16:57.599
it mainly buys from India

00:16:57.600 --> 00:16:58.533
processes it,

00:16:58.533 --> 00:16:59.499
and then

00:16:59.500 --> 00:17:01.233
packages or assembles it into various hair accessories

00:17:01.233 --> 00:17:02.533
before exporting it globally.

00:17:02.533 --> 00:17:03.633
Generally, it first goes through China

00:17:03.633 --> 00:17:04.599
before being exported.

00:17:04.600 --> 00:17:05.100
So you see, in 2023

00:17:05.100 --> 00:17:07.233
North Korea's largest import

00:17:07.233 --> 00:17:08.133
was hair

00:17:08.133 --> 00:17:10.066
The next country we're going to talk about

00:17:10.066 --> 00:17:11.033
that was sanctioned actually

00:17:11.033 --> 00:17:13.133
had successful negotiations before

00:17:13.133 --> 00:17:14.166
and more than once

00:17:14.166 --> 00:17:15.199
that is Iran

00:17:17.033 --> 00:17:18.833
We've discussed the Iranian economy separately;

00:17:18.833 --> 00:17:21.100
today we'll mainly talk about the sanctions

00:17:21.966 --> 00:17:22.899
In 1979,

00:17:22.899 --> 00:17:25.133
Khomeini, the Islamic leader, had just successfully

00:17:25.133 --> 00:17:26.366
overthrown the Pahlavi dynasty

00:17:26.366 --> 00:17:27.966
and established the Islamic Republic of Iran.

00:17:27.966 --> 00:17:29.466
The Pahlavi king fled overseas,

00:17:30.066 --> 00:17:32.366
and then the famous hostage crisis occurred.

00:17:32.366 --> 00:17:33.233
A group of Islamic students

00:17:33.233 --> 00:17:35.066
stormed the US embassy in Tehran,

00:17:35.066 --> 00:17:37.433
taking dozens of American diplomats hostage and

00:17:37.433 --> 00:17:39.266
demanding the US hand over Pahlavi.

00:17:39.266 --> 00:17:41.099
At that time, relations between Iran and the US were very tense,

00:17:41.100 --> 00:17:42.299
and the US imposed

00:17:42.299 --> 00:17:43.466
very severe economic sanctions on Iran

00:17:43.466 --> 00:17:46.100
freezing $8.1 billion of Iranian assets in the US.

00:17:46.133 --> 00:17:47.966
This was extremely devastating for Iran at the time,

00:17:47.966 --> 00:17:49.133
and it also prohibited many of

00:17:49.133 --> 00:17:50.500
Iran's economic and trade exchanges

00:17:50.500 --> 00:17:51.366
You have to understand

00:17:51.366 --> 00:17:51.966
back then,

00:17:51.966 --> 00:17:53.133
economic sanctions weren't

00:17:53.133 --> 00:17:54.299
as common as they are now;

00:17:54.299 --> 00:17:56.466
the US hadn't used them much except for Cuba.

00:17:56.466 --> 00:17:58.299
Iran honestly wasn’t prepared for that tactic

00:17:58.299 --> 00:17:59.933
and unsure of its consequences

00:17:59.933 --> 00:18:00.866
so they were extremely cautious,

00:18:00.866 --> 00:18:01.433
employing

00:18:01.433 --> 00:18:02.766
various negotiations

00:18:02.766 --> 00:18:03.466
and threats .

00:18:03.466 --> 00:18:04.233
After more than a year,

00:18:04.233 --> 00:18:06.133
Iran released the US embassy personnel.

00:18:06.133 --> 00:18:07.533
This action, while contributing

00:18:07.533 --> 00:18:09.133
to the sanctions, can indeed be considered

00:18:09.133 --> 00:18:10.433
a short-lived

00:18:10.433 --> 00:18:11.933
but successful case.

00:18:12.899 --> 00:18:14.266
In the following decades,

00:18:14.266 --> 00:18:16.533
As the Iran-Iraq War progressed, support for regional armed groups

00:18:16.533 --> 00:18:18.433
missile programs, and other initiatives gradually came to light

00:18:18.433 --> 00:18:20.733
the US began to intensify its sanctions against Iran.

00:18:20.733 --> 00:18:22.700
However, this period was relatively restrained,

00:18:22.700 --> 00:18:23.700
primarily targeting individuals,

00:18:23.700 --> 00:18:24.500
armed groups

00:18:24.500 --> 00:18:25.833
or oil companies.

00:18:25.833 --> 00:18:27.533
The real large-scale sanctions against Iran

00:18:27.533 --> 00:18:29.133
began after 2000, when

00:18:30.066 --> 00:18:31.166
there were indications that

00:18:31.166 --> 00:18:33.033
Iran was secretly conducting nuclear tests

00:18:33.033 --> 00:18:34.966
Once nuclear weapons are involved,

00:18:34.966 --> 00:18:36.666
global sanctions intensify,

00:18:36.666 --> 00:18:37.499
just like with North Korea

00:18:37.500 --> 00:18:38.299
Not only the US,

00:18:38.299 --> 00:18:38.899
but also the EU

00:18:38.899 --> 00:18:40.866
and the UN Security Council began sanctioning Iran.

00:18:40.866 --> 00:18:41.766
And this time, I'm telling you,

00:18:41.766 --> 00:18:43.266
the US has pulled a more ruthless move

00:18:43.266 --> 00:18:45.033
the second form of sanctions.

00:18:45.033 --> 00:18:45.733
This is crucial

00:18:45.733 --> 00:18:46.500
and became a hallmark of its subsequent

00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:48.233
comprehensive economic sanctions.

00:18:48.233 --> 00:18:49.700
This is secondary sanctions.

00:18:51.299 --> 00:18:52.533
What are secondary sanctions?

00:18:52.533 --> 00:18:53.133
It's not just about

00:18:53.133 --> 00:18:54.699
escalating the situation.

00:18:54.700 --> 00:18:56.566
It means not only that I won't do business with you anymore,

00:18:56.566 --> 00:18:58.100
but I'll also threaten others

00:18:58.100 --> 00:18:59.933
if I find out anyone

00:18:59.933 --> 00:19:01.966
dares to do business with them, I'll deal with them too.

00:19:01.966 --> 00:19:03.333
It's like a group of kids.

00:19:03.333 --> 00:19:05.900
Previous sanctions were like the US threatening Iran, saying

00:19:05.933 --> 00:19:06.966
"I'm not playing with you anymore

00:19:06.966 --> 00:19:08.166
you can't touch anything I've used,

00:19:08.166 --> 00:19:09.033
any toys I've played with,

00:19:09.033 --> 00:19:10.566
or any seat I've sat in.

00:19:10.566 --> 00:19:12.033
You 'd better avoid me."

00:19:12.033 --> 00:19:14.333
See, that threat sounds very tough.

00:19:14.333 --> 00:19:16.266
But even with its strong economy, the US only

00:19:16.266 --> 00:19:18.099
accounts for a quarter of the world's GDP.

00:19:18.100 --> 00:19:19.566
If you just threaten to stop playing with them,

00:19:19.566 --> 00:19:22.533
Iran can still play with the other three-quarters of the kids, right?

00:19:22.533 --> 00:19:25.366
 It can still play with Europe, Russia, Japan,

00:19:25.366 --> 00:19:26.366
and do business with those countries.

00:19:26.366 --> 00:19:28.733
So the effect of those previous sanctions wasn't very obvious.

00:19:28.733 --> 00:19:30.066
But this time, secondary sanctions

00:19:30.066 --> 00:19:31.766
are like the US saying,

00:19:31.766 --> 00:19:32.833
"Not only am I not playing with Iran,

00:19:32.833 --> 00:19:33.533
but you other countries

00:19:33.533 --> 00:19:34.466
Europe, Russia, Japan

00:19:34.466 --> 00:19:35.733
can't play with Iran either.

00:19:35.733 --> 00:19:36.933
Anyone who dares to play with them,

00:19:37.033 --> 00:19:37.833
I'll deal with them"

00:19:38.700 --> 00:19:40.733
You see, the US is the leader of the kids, right

00:19:40.733 --> 00:19:41.533
He also has the largest muscle mass.

00:19:41.533 --> 00:19:42.099
Other kids

00:19:42.100 --> 00:19:42.733
generally

00:19:42.733 --> 00:19:44.333
don't need to go against the US.

00:19:44.333 --> 00:19:46.366
Anyway, I'm probably not very familiar with Iran

00:19:46.366 --> 00:19:47.866
so I won't play with Iran

00:19:49.333 --> 00:19:50.366
You see, secondary sanctions

00:19:50.366 --> 00:19:52.899
are about threatening other countries to isolate together

00:19:52.899 --> 00:19:54.466
which greatly increases the success rate of the sanctions.

00:19:54.466 --> 00:19:55.166
For the US,

00:19:55.166 --> 00:19:56.499
it's like leverage

00:19:56.500 --> 00:19:58.366
the impact is much greater.

00:19:58.366 --> 00:19:59.500
Let's analyse further.

00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:00.766
Actually , there's a prerequisite

00:20:00.766 --> 00:20:01.933
for implementing secondary sanctions

00:20:01.933 --> 00:20:03.499
the US

00:20:03.500 --> 00:20:04.933
itself must first be extremely powerful.

00:20:04.933 --> 00:20:06.699
Look at the number of sanctions in history

00:20:06.700 --> 00:20:07.899
you'll find that after year 2000

00:20:07.899 --> 00:20:09.033
it increased exponentially.

00:20:09.033 --> 00:20:09.633
You might ask why

00:20:09.633 --> 00:20:10.566
Is it because

00:20:10.566 --> 00:20:12.066
the world is much more chaotic after year 2000

00:20:12.066 --> 00:20:12.666
Oh, not necessarily

00:20:12.666 --> 00:20:13.533
One major reason

00:20:13.533 --> 00:20:15.266
is that the world has shifted from a bipolar to

00:20:15.266 --> 00:20:16.633
a unipolar system,

00:20:17.433 --> 00:20:18.499
U.S. hegemony

00:20:18.500 --> 00:20:19.466
making it easier for the US

00:20:19.566 --> 00:20:20.733
to implement secondary sanctions.

00:20:20.733 --> 00:20:22.033
This significantly increases the effectiveness of

00:20:22.033 --> 00:20:24.566
US sanctions, leading to a greater frequency of their use.

00:20:24.566 --> 00:20:25.899
For example, Venezuela, which we just discussed,

00:20:25.899 --> 00:20:27.299
is severely restricted by sanctions,

00:20:27.299 --> 00:20:28.699
primarily due to secondary sanctions

00:20:28.700 --> 00:20:29.466
not trade, but

00:20:29.466 --> 00:20:30.966
financial secondary sanction

00:20:31.066 --> 00:20:31.833
Any other country

00:20:31.833 --> 00:20:33.766
trading with Venezuela

00:20:33.766 --> 00:20:35.433
cannot access US banks. 

00:20:35.433 --> 00:20:36.633
This has a very wide reach,

00:20:36.633 --> 00:20:37.833
resulting in almost no one

00:20:37.833 --> 00:20:39.166
daring to have financial dealings with Venezuela,

00:20:39.166 --> 00:20:40.733
at least not openly.

00:20:41.466 --> 00:20:41.966
In short, 

00:20:41.966 --> 00:20:44.466
in 2010, the US imposed even harsher sanctions on Iran

00:20:44.466 --> 00:20:45.733
The UN sanctions

00:20:45.733 --> 00:20:47.466
dealt a heavy blow to Iran

00:20:47.466 --> 00:20:49.100
forcing it back to the negotiating table.

00:20:49.100 --> 00:20:51.433
Starting in 2013, negotiation with various major powers

00:20:51.433 --> 00:20:52.533
culminated in the 

00:20:52.533 --> 00:20:54.666
signing of the famous Iran nuclear deal in 2015.

00:20:54.666 --> 00:20:56.733
Iran agreed to limit some of its nuclear activities

00:20:56.733 --> 00:20:58.133
in exchange for a reduction in sanctions

00:20:58.133 --> 00:20:58.833
This agreement

00:20:58.833 --> 00:20:59.333
can be considered

00:20:59.333 --> 00:21:02.033
a highlight in the history of economic sanctions negotiations

00:21:02.033 --> 00:21:04.133
sanctions finally led to peace, and

00:21:04.133 --> 00:21:05.266
a major agreement was reached.

00:21:05.266 --> 00:21:07.433
Iran did indeed receive some economic relief,

00:21:07.433 --> 00:21:08.466
with some assets unfrozen

00:21:08.466 --> 00:21:09.900
and oil exports beginning to recover

00:21:09.933 --> 00:21:11.366
However, this didn't last long.

00:21:11.366 --> 00:21:12.533
Then came the revelation

00:21:13.066 --> 00:21:13.833
 

00:21:13.833 --> 00:21:14.933
the previous agreement with Iran

00:21:14.933 --> 00:21:16.299
was a terrible deal, and

00:21:16.299 --> 00:21:17.099
they reneged

00:21:17.100 --> 00:21:18.533
reinstating and even

00:21:18.533 --> 00:21:19.466
intensifying sanctions against Iran , 

00:21:19.466 --> 00:21:21.533
causing a precipitous drop in oil exports.

00:21:21.533 --> 00:21:24.233
This year, negotiations between Iran and the UN are on the verge of collapse.

00:21:24.233 --> 00:21:25.633
The UN reinstated sanctions 

00:21:25.633 --> 00:21:27.166
against Iran in September.

00:21:28.200 --> 00:21:29.766
We've discussed Iran's methods of evading sanctions

00:21:29.766 --> 00:21:30.866
in detail before.

00:21:30.866 --> 00:21:31.633
Over time,

00:21:31.633 --> 00:21:32.966
it has developed

00:21:32.966 --> 00:21:34.500
its own countermeasures system.

00:21:34.500 --> 00:21:35.933
Through its ghost fleet at sea and

00:21:35.933 --> 00:21:36.899
smuggling networks, it

00:21:36.899 --> 00:21:38.733
has mitigated the intensity of sanctions to some extent

00:21:38.733 --> 00:21:40.700
significantly strengthening

00:21:40.700 --> 00:21:41.833
its two major economic arms

00:21:41.833 --> 00:21:43.266
the Revolutionary Guard and the Foundation.

00:21:43.266 --> 00:21:46.333
However, its overall economy is severely suppressed

00:21:46.333 --> 00:21:47.333
under the heavy pressure of US sanctions

00:21:47.333 --> 00:21:48.500
especially after the pandemic,

00:21:48.500 --> 00:21:50.333
plunging into a severe food crisis,

00:21:50.333 --> 00:21:51.133
energy crisis

00:21:51.133 --> 00:21:52.299
and hyperinflation.

00:21:52.299 --> 00:21:53.866
The riyal's continued plunge in exchange rate

00:21:55.100 --> 00:21:56.433
confirms

00:21:56.433 --> 00:21:57.466
our earlier theory that

00:21:57.466 --> 00:22:00.066
sanctions further suppress Iran's lower classes.

00:22:00.066 --> 00:22:00.733
Even if you believe

00:22:00.733 --> 00:22:02.866
this is a necessary price to pay to achieve our goals,

00:22:02.866 --> 00:22:04.899
and that the lower classes must be suppressed to a certain extent

00:22:04.899 --> 00:22:06.266
before they can rise up and make changes

00:22:06.266 --> 00:22:06.866
However,

00:22:06.866 --> 00:22:08.933
there's an even harsher reality

00:22:08.966 --> 00:22:09.833
often,

00:22:09.833 --> 00:22:10.933
and most of the time,

00:22:10.933 --> 00:22:12.066
sanctions not only fail

00:22:12.066 --> 00:22:14.166
to create internal conflict within the sanctioned country, 

00:22:14.166 --> 00:22:15.466
but their propaganda actually

00:22:15.466 --> 00:22:17.899
makes the lower classes more hostile to the sanctioning country.

00:22:17.899 --> 00:22:18.966
The sanctioned government

00:22:18.966 --> 00:22:20.566
often uses this environment to

00:22:20.566 --> 00:22:22.266
further strengthen its authoritarianism

00:22:22.266 --> 00:22:24.166
This has a counterproductive effect,

00:22:24.166 --> 00:22:25.833
making change more difficult,

00:22:25.833 --> 00:22:27.066
and the main consequence of sanctions

00:22:27.066 --> 00:22:27.500
becomes

00:22:27.500 --> 00:22:29.199
simply punishing and suppressing

00:22:29.200 --> 00:22:30.900
the lower classes of the sanctioned country.

00:22:38.100 --> 00:22:38.866
Okay, next,

00:22:38.866 --> 00:22:40.866
the last sanctioned country we'll discuss

00:22:40.866 --> 00:22:41.933
is a comprehensive summary 

00:22:41.933 --> 00:22:44.566
of all the methods we've mentioned.

00:22:44.566 --> 00:22:45.500
The US and EU

00:22:45.500 --> 00:22:47.500
have basically used all their sanctioning tactics

00:22:47.500 --> 00:22:48.333
over the years on it.

00:22:48.333 --> 00:22:49.533
I'm sure you've guessed it

00:22:49.533 --> 00:22:50.766
it's Russia.

00:22:51.966 --> 00:22:53.333
Before the Russo-Ukrainian war, 

00:22:53.333 --> 00:22:55.366
in 2014, Russia annexed Crimea, and many countries and regions, including

00:22:55.366 --> 00:22:57.433
the US, EU, Canada, Australia, and

00:22:57.433 --> 00:22:58.033
Japan,

00:22:58.033 --> 00:23:00.233
imposed sanctions on Russia.

00:23:00.233 --> 00:23:02.366
At the time, this was considered very severe;

00:23:02.566 --> 00:23:04.100
in terms of the number of sanctioned items, 

00:23:04.100 --> 00:23:05.133
the largest at that time was Iran

00:23:05.133 --> 00:23:06.533
has 3,616 sanctions,

00:23:06.533 --> 00:23:07.699
while Russia ranks second

00:23:07.700 --> 00:23:09.000
with 2,695 items.

00:23:09.000 --> 00:23:10.033
That sounds like a lot, right?

00:23:10.033 --> 00:23:12.633
But compared to subsequent sanctions, it's just a drop in the ocean.

00:23:13.333 --> 00:23:14.166
After the Russia-Ukraine war,

00:23:14.166 --> 00:23:16.099
the number of sanctions imposed on Russia increased tenfold,

00:23:16.100 --> 00:23:17.433
exceeding 25,000.

00:23:17.433 --> 00:23:19.599
Global countries imposed

00:23:19.600 --> 00:23:20.366
the largest and

00:23:20.366 --> 00:23:21.766
most numerous sanctions in history

00:23:22.733 --> 00:23:23.633
I roughly divide the sanctions against Russia 

00:23:23.633 --> 00:23:24.933
into several categories.

00:23:24.933 --> 00:23:26.733
First, I think everyone can answer immediately

00:23:26.733 --> 00:23:28.533
those targeting individuals and entities.

00:23:28.533 --> 00:23:29.699
Previously, most countries only

00:23:29.700 --> 00:23:31.166
symbolically imposed these sanctions, but

00:23:31.166 --> 00:23:32.166
they were actually quite effective

00:23:32.166 --> 00:23:32.966
for Russia

00:23:32.966 --> 00:23:33.566
because Russia

00:23:33.566 --> 00:23:36.166
has many very wealthy oligarchs who

00:23:36.166 --> 00:23:37.499
keep their money in overseas banks

00:23:37.500 --> 00:23:39.199
or hide it overseas. 

00:23:39.200 --> 00:23:40.700
This includes bank assets,

00:23:40.700 --> 00:23:41.899
apartments, and yachts.

00:23:41.899 --> 00:23:43.933
It's estimated that a total

00:23:43.933 --> 00:23:45.233
of $3 billion in assets belonging to Russian oligarchs has been frozen. 

00:23:45.799 --> 00:23:46.399
While this amount

00:23:46.399 --> 00:23:47.766
may seem small in the grand scheme of things

00:23:47.766 --> 00:23:49.433
The impact on Russia’s economy

00:23:49.433 --> 00:23:50.199
was certainly small in proportion.

00:23:50.200 --> 00:23:51.333
But it did hit the top levels 

00:23:51.333 --> 00:23:53.000
and elites of Russia with

00:23:53.000 --> 00:23:53.833
remarkable precision

00:23:53.833 --> 00:23:54.933
even restricting their travel abroad.

00:23:54.933 --> 00:23:57.533
These wealthy individuals are likely furious.

00:23:57.533 --> 00:24:00.433
The second major sanction against Russia is SWIFT.

00:24:00.566 --> 00:24:02.233
Most people are familiar with it

00:24:02.233 --> 00:24:05.566
SWIFT, short for Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunication.

00:24:05.566 --> 00:24:06.133
Simply put,

00:24:06.133 --> 00:24:07.566
it's a standardised language

00:24:07.566 --> 00:24:08.566
for global 

00:24:08.566 --> 00:24:09.600
interbank transfers

00:24:09.600 --> 00:24:11.299
For example, international transfers

00:24:11.299 --> 00:24:12.699
use a SWIFT code.

00:24:12.700 --> 00:24:13.899
The SWIFT system

00:24:13.899 --> 00:24:15.699
connects over 11,000 entities worldwide

00:24:15.700 --> 00:24:16.966
we won't go into detail today.

00:24:16.966 --> 00:24:17.799
In short,

00:24:17.799 --> 00:24:19.633
most cross-border transfers between banks

00:24:19.633 --> 00:24:21.399
must use the SWIFT standard.

00:24:21.399 --> 00:24:22.099
Generally, 

00:24:22.100 --> 00:24:23.233
if you don't use SWIFT,

00:24:23.233 --> 00:24:24.233
the receiving bank won't accept it.

00:24:24.233 --> 00:24:25.399
As part of the sanctions,

00:24:25.399 --> 00:24:26.899
there are 45 Russian banks

00:24:26.899 --> 00:24:28.233
and 4 Belarusian banks

00:24:28.233 --> 00:24:30.399
have been banned from using SWIFT for international payments

00:24:30.399 --> 00:24:32.899
effectively blocking most Russian banks.

00:24:32.899 --> 00:24:34.133
Note that SWIFT doesn't completely block

00:24:34.133 --> 00:24:35.766
overseas funding channels

00:24:35.766 --> 00:24:37.633
After all, it's just a standardised language.

00:24:37.633 --> 00:24:39.899
It’s like I’m cutting off your contact with the outside world

00:24:39.899 --> 00:24:41.099
I’m not locking you up

00:24:41.100 --> 00:24:42.200
or confiscate your phone

00:24:42.200 --> 00:24:44.166
but many mainstream chat apps would become unusable

00:24:44.166 --> 00:24:45.099
not even WeChat.

00:24:45.100 --> 00:24:45.600
This way

00:24:45.600 --> 00:24:46.700
would significantly increase the cost

00:24:46.700 --> 00:24:48.133
of contacting others. 

00:24:48.133 --> 00:24:49.133
You'd either have to write a letter, 

00:24:49.133 --> 00:24:49.799
make a phone call

00:24:49.799 --> 00:24:51.399
or develop your own APP

00:24:51.399 --> 00:24:53.233
which would require the other party to cooperate by

00:24:53.233 --> 00:24:54.966
writing letters, making phone calls, or using your APP

00:24:54.966 --> 00:24:56.033
very inconvenient, right?

00:24:56.033 --> 00:24:58.133
From a macro perspective, this inconvenience translates

00:24:58.133 --> 00:24:59.966
into huge economic losses

00:24:59.966 --> 00:25:00.633
and costs. 

00:25:00.633 --> 00:25:01.966
So how does Russia retaliate

00:25:01.966 --> 00:25:03.366
against such economic sanctions?

00:25:04.600 --> 00:25:05.933
In fact, it developed its own system

00:25:05.933 --> 00:25:08.566
as early as 2014, the alternative to SWIFT

00:25:08.566 --> 00:25:09.633
is called SPFS.

00:25:09.633 --> 00:25:10.799
In the example we just discussed,

00:25:10.799 --> 00:25:12.099
it's like they developed their own

00:25:12.100 --> 00:25:13.100
chat app.

00:25:13.100 --> 00:25:14.899
Developing such a system isn't difficult.

00:25:14.899 --> 00:25:16.899
SWIFT itself isn't user-friendly;

00:25:16.899 --> 00:25:18.133
it's slow and inefficient.

00:25:18.133 --> 00:25:19.533
The key is that everyone uses it

00:25:19.533 --> 00:25:20.733
creating a network effect.

00:25:20.733 --> 00:25:22.733
Even if Russia's SPFS system

00:25:22.733 --> 00:25:23.633
is well-developed,

00:25:23.633 --> 00:25:24.433
the biggest challenge is

00:25:24.433 --> 00:25:26.633
getting the other party’s banks to trust the system

00:25:26.700 --> 00:25:27.433
and actually use it

00:25:27.433 --> 00:25:28.399
and that takes time.

00:25:28.399 --> 00:25:30.433
Currently about a quarter of cross-border payments

00:25:30.433 --> 00:25:33.333
 in Russia use SPFS

00:25:33.333 --> 00:25:34.299
Other methods

00:25:34.299 --> 00:25:35.099
include using

00:25:35.100 --> 00:25:36.933
a friendly third-country bank,

00:25:36.933 --> 00:25:37.933
or cryptocurrencies

00:25:37.933 --> 00:25:39.299
they've also developed their own stablecoins

00:25:39.299 --> 00:25:40.533
In general, excluding SWIFT

00:25:40.533 --> 00:25:42.833
has significant impact on Russia's financial system.

00:25:42.833 --> 00:25:44.766
The third major sanction against Russia

00:25:44.766 --> 00:25:46.533
is the freezing of official assets,

00:25:47.200 --> 00:25:48.166
primarily

00:25:48.166 --> 00:25:50.166
the assets of the Russian central bank,

00:25:50.166 --> 00:25:51.166
namely its foreign exchange reserves.

00:25:51.166 --> 00:25:52.333
As mentioned earlier when discussing

00:25:52.333 --> 00:25:53.333
Cuba and Iran

00:25:53.333 --> 00:25:54.533
the US and Europe

00:25:54.533 --> 00:25:56.299
freeze all

00:25:56.299 --> 00:25:57.199
assets in banks and financial institutions

00:25:57.200 --> 00:25:58.899
within a country they

00:25:58.899 --> 00:25:59.566
can reach

00:25:59.566 --> 00:26:00.500
This time,

00:26:00.500 --> 00:26:01.799
approximately $300 billion of Russia's assets were frozen,

00:26:01.799 --> 00:26:03.399
roughly half of its foreign exchange reserves.

00:26:03.399 --> 00:26:04.799
And do you know which country 

00:26:04.799 --> 00:26:05.933
held the majority of this frozen money?

00:26:05.933 --> 00:26:06.899
You probably wouldn't guess it

00:26:06.899 --> 00:26:08.233
it's Belgium

00:26:08.333 --> 00:26:09.633
 Why Belgium?

00:26:09.633 --> 00:26:11.133
Because Russia's central bank and

00:26:11.133 --> 00:26:13.133
its foreign exchange reserves aren't all cash;

00:26:13.133 --> 00:26:14.533
they've purchased a large amount of financial assets.

00:26:14.533 --> 00:26:15.633
For example, European

00:26:15.633 --> 00:26:16.399
and American bonds,

00:26:16.399 --> 00:26:17.566
especially European bonds,

00:26:17.566 --> 00:26:20.233
all need to be cleared

00:26:20.233 --> 00:26:21.000
or managed

00:26:21.000 --> 00:26:22.099
by a company called Euroclear.

00:26:22.100 --> 00:26:24.166
Therefore, the European bonds purchased by the Russian central bank

00:26:24.166 --> 00:26:26.833
all had to go through the Belgian company Euroclear.

00:26:26.833 --> 00:26:28.166
Now, all of these have been frozen. 

00:26:28.166 --> 00:26:29.599
With the central bank's foreign exchange reserves frozen,

00:26:29.600 --> 00:26:31.533
it's difficult for it to freely adjust the exchange rate.

00:26:31.533 --> 00:26:33.433
This is why you see the ruble falling so sharply

00:26:33.433 --> 00:26:34.933
at the beginning of the war.

00:26:35.466 --> 00:26:37.200
However, Russia has one major advantage

00:26:37.200 --> 00:26:38.500
it has a money-printing machine

00:26:38.500 --> 00:26:39.500
its energy resources.

00:26:39.533 --> 00:26:41.399
Russia's annual energy exports

00:26:41.399 --> 00:26:43.099
can earn approximately $200-300 billion

00:26:43.100 --> 00:26:44.833
So, the freezing of $300 billion in its central bank's reserves has

00:26:44.833 --> 00:26:45.766
a significant short-term impact

00:26:45.766 --> 00:26:46.499
but frankly, 

00:26:46.500 --> 00:26:48.799
in the long run, it will not be difficult for it to recover. 

00:26:48.799 --> 00:26:50.299
The next direction of sanctions, 

00:26:50.299 --> 00:26:52.166
is also the trade sanctions we mentioned earlier.

00:26:52.166 --> 00:26:54.199
For Russia, it’s basically targeting its money-printing machine

00:26:54.200 --> 00:26:55.299
oil and gas.

00:26:55.299 --> 00:26:57.199
If you want to restrict Russian oil and gas,

00:26:57.200 --> 00:26:59.299
the sanctioning country also faces difficulties

00:26:59.299 --> 00:27:00.766
The EU is far too dependent on

00:27:00.766 --> 00:27:01.799
Russian energy.

00:27:01.799 --> 00:27:02.166
You see,

00:27:02.166 --> 00:27:04.033
previously 45% of its natural gas,

00:27:04.033 --> 00:27:05.633
almost half, came from Russia.

00:27:05.633 --> 00:27:08.133
This is the kind of move that could hurt the enemy but end up hurting yourself even more

00:27:08.133 --> 00:27:08.633
Frankly,

00:27:08.633 --> 00:27:10.099
the EU just wanted to prove

00:27:10.100 --> 00:27:10.933
itself, right?

00:27:10.933 --> 00:27:12.133
So you see, in 2022,

00:27:12.133 --> 00:27:13.199
most European countries

00:27:13.200 --> 00:27:14.733
were also facing their own energy crises

00:27:15.766 --> 00:27:17.766
And because Russia's natural

00:27:17.766 --> 00:27:19.133
gas and oil exports were so large,

00:27:19.133 --> 00:27:20.433
the US and Europe didn't dare to directly ban them

00:27:20.433 --> 00:27:22.199
for fear of triggering a global energy crisis.

00:27:22.200 --> 00:27:23.500
So how did they finally decide to impose sanctions?

00:27:23.500 --> 00:27:25.299
Russian can still export oil

00:27:25.299 --> 00:27:26.933
but all seaborne oil shipments

00:27:26.933 --> 00:27:28.399
were subject to a price cap.

00:27:28.399 --> 00:27:29.799
This cap was set at $60 per barrel

00:27:29.799 --> 00:27:30.966
at the end of 2022,

00:27:30.966 --> 00:27:32.900
roughly 85% of the market price at the time.

00:27:33.033 --> 00:27:34.333
The aim was

00:27:34.333 --> 00:27:36.133
to restrict Russian revenue

00:27:36.133 --> 00:27:38.133
without significantly impacting

00:27:38.133 --> 00:27:39.366
global energy prices . 

00:27:39.366 --> 00:27:41.800
And do you know who the biggest beneficiary was?

00:27:41.899 --> 00:27:43.166
We've mentioned it multiple times

00:27:43.166 --> 00:27:44.099
It's india

00:27:45.100 --> 00:27:47.033
When the West first proposed sanctions on Russian oil,

00:27:47.033 --> 00:27:47.799
India objected,

00:27:47.799 --> 00:27:48.799
saying, "you can impose sanctions

00:27:48.799 --> 00:27:50.299
but I won't!

00:27:50.299 --> 00:27:51.899
I don't agree to the price cap! "

00:27:52.000 --> 00:27:52.966
As a result, India began

00:27:52.966 --> 00:27:54.566
importing large quantities of Russian energy,

00:27:54.566 --> 00:27:57.799
roughly 20 times the amount it imported before the war.

00:27:57.799 --> 00:27:58.366
Actually, for the past 2 years

00:27:58.366 --> 00:28:00.133
you can see that India's economy has developed very rapidly

00:28:00.133 --> 00:28:02.799
which is largely related

00:28:02.799 --> 00:28:03.699
to the cheap energy imports from Russia

00:28:03.700 --> 00:28:04.233
Of course,

00:28:04.233 --> 00:28:06.333
India's non-participation in sanctions also has its costs.

00:28:06.333 --> 00:28:07.299
What are these costs?

00:28:07.299 --> 00:28:08.399
Secondary sanctions.

00:28:08.433 --> 00:28:08.933
Look at the US

00:28:08.933 --> 00:28:11.533
this year, it first imposed a 25% basic tariff on India,

00:28:11.533 --> 00:28:12.766
and a few days ago Trump said that

00:28:12.766 --> 00:28:14.499
because India bought so much Russian oil

00:28:14.500 --> 00:28:15.599
and did not comply with the price cap

00:28:15.600 --> 00:28:18.100
he would impose an additional 25% tariff on it

00:28:19.166 --> 00:28:19.766
In general,

00:28:19.766 --> 00:28:21.566
one of the ways Russia circumvents

00:28:21.566 --> 00:28:22.200
Western trade and

00:28:22.200 --> 00:28:23.866
oil sanctions

00:28:23.866 --> 00:28:24.899
is by selling to India

00:28:24.899 --> 00:28:25.533
and China.

00:28:25.533 --> 00:28:27.033
Its energy exports will certainly be suppressed

00:28:27.033 --> 00:28:28.199
but it still has considerable revenue

00:28:28.200 --> 00:28:29.766
which has become an important source of income

00:28:29.766 --> 00:28:30.633
for it to resist sanctions.

00:28:30.633 --> 00:28:32.933
At the same time, Russia also engages in a lot of smuggling

00:28:32.933 --> 00:28:35.133
This is the border between Georgia and Russia.

00:28:35.133 --> 00:28:36.799
The long line of trucks here

00:28:36.799 --> 00:28:39.099
is all waiting to trade with Russia.

00:28:39.166 --> 00:28:40.433
Hidden among them are many

00:28:40.433 --> 00:28:43.133
luxury cars like Mercedes-Benz and BMW, which are subject to sanctions.

00:28:44.133 --> 00:28:45.733
If you only look at official data,

00:28:45.733 --> 00:28:46.433
you'll see that

00:28:46.433 --> 00:28:48.199
Georgia's trade deficit in the past two years

00:28:48.200 --> 00:28:48.899
is alarmingly high.

00:28:48.899 --> 00:28:51.166
Its imports far exceed its exports.

00:28:51.166 --> 00:28:51.833
Why?

00:28:51.833 --> 00:28:53.799
Well, not only have imports increased, but

00:28:53.799 --> 00:28:55.033
exports have also increased.

00:28:55.033 --> 00:28:56.966
However, these are all smuggled into Russia and

00:28:56.966 --> 00:28:58.299
not recorded in the official accounts,

00:28:58.299 --> 00:28:59.266
so the officially reported

00:28:59.299 --> 00:29:00.766
trade deficit appears significantly larger.

00:29:00.766 --> 00:29:01.733
In essence, this means

00:29:01.733 --> 00:29:04.200
Russia is using Georgia for transshipment

00:29:04.200 --> 00:29:05.166
to evade sanctions. 

00:29:06.133 --> 00:29:06.933
Besides the official sanctions

00:29:06.933 --> 00:29:08.333
we just mentioned, Russia

00:29:08.333 --> 00:29:10.166
has also been impacted by another factor

00:29:10.166 --> 00:29:11.299
You could also call it a sanction, which

00:29:11.299 --> 00:29:12.133
I find quite interesting.

00:29:12.133 --> 00:29:14.933
It's a self-sanction from overseas companies.

00:29:15.566 --> 00:29:17.166
Many Western multinational brands,

00:29:17.166 --> 00:29:19.166
even though they can still operate legally in Russia

00:29:19.166 --> 00:29:20.699
are worried about public opinion risks

00:29:20.700 --> 00:29:22.000
so they say, "I have to withdraw."

00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:23.833
They sanction themselves by

00:29:23.833 --> 00:29:25.133
moving their businesses out of Russia.

00:29:25.133 --> 00:29:26.299
Imagine, within a week,

00:29:26.299 --> 00:29:28.433
all the big brands we're familiar with are gone,

00:29:28.433 --> 00:29:29.333
all closed down.

00:29:29.333 --> 00:29:30.733
The impact is quite significant.

00:29:30.733 --> 00:29:32.133
However, if you think about it carefully,

00:29:32.133 --> 00:29:33.133
it doesn't mean that

00:29:33.133 --> 00:29:34.966
a vacuum immediately appeared in these industries.

00:29:34.966 --> 00:29:36.500
The original physical stores,

00:29:36.500 --> 00:29:37.299
employees,

00:29:37.299 --> 00:29:38.833
and supply chains are still there;

00:29:38.833 --> 00:29:39.700
the companies have left.

00:29:39.700 --> 00:29:41.066
But what can Russia do?

00:29:41.066 --> 00:29:42.200
It can change the name but not the substance.

00:29:42.200 --> 00:29:43.100
I can go with the original team.

00:29:43.100 --> 00:29:45.299
immediately set up a new Russian knock-off

00:29:45.299 --> 00:29:46.099
and continue operating

00:29:46.433 --> 00:29:47.133
So at this time

00:29:47.133 --> 00:29:48.366
There are many

00:29:48.366 --> 00:29:50.133
comical knock-off brands appeared in Russia.

00:29:50.133 --> 00:29:52.566
The original Starbucks became Stars Coffee,

00:29:52.566 --> 00:29:54.366
Zara became Maag

00:29:54.366 --> 00:29:56.000
Coca-Cola became Dobri Cola,

00:29:56.033 --> 00:29:56.833
and many more.

00:29:58.299 --> 00:30:00.199
We've discussed so many examples

00:30:00.200 --> 00:30:02.333
but there's a fundamental principle about sanctions

00:30:02.333 --> 00:30:03.433
which is that sanctions

00:30:03.433 --> 00:30:05.699
are often more effective in the short term.

00:30:05.700 --> 00:30:06.166
Economic sanctions

00:30:06.166 --> 00:30:08.133
frequently catch countries off guard.

00:30:08.133 --> 00:30:09.433
Once the sanctioned country recovers and

00:30:09.433 --> 00:30:10.166
adjusts, and

00:30:10.166 --> 00:30:11.233
a new system is established,

00:30:11.233 --> 00:30:12.733
the marginal effect diminishes sharply.

00:30:13.433 --> 00:30:15.399
Look at why sanctions against Cuba and North Korea

00:30:15.399 --> 00:30:16.133
haven't had such a significant impact.

00:30:16.133 --> 00:30:17.133
They've been under sanctions for years and

00:30:17.133 --> 00:30:17.933
have long since recovered

00:30:17.933 --> 00:30:20.133
They've figured out their economic structures, resource channels, 

00:30:20.133 --> 00:30:21.199
and alternative solutions,

00:30:21.200 --> 00:30:22.700
so they're not so afraid of sanctions.

00:30:22.700 --> 00:30:24.799
The two successful negotiations between the US and Iran

00:30:24.799 --> 00:30:25.933
were both quite sudden,

00:30:25.933 --> 00:30:27.233
catching Iran off guard.

00:30:27.233 --> 00:30:28.100
As for Russia,

00:30:28.100 --> 00:30:30.399
although Western sanctions seem sudden

00:30:30.399 --> 00:30:32.233
but you can see that Russia

00:30:32.233 --> 00:30:34.833
secretly began preparing to counter them as early as 2014.

00:30:35.833 --> 00:30:37.966
Sanctions are most effective when

00:30:37.966 --> 00:30:38.566
the sanctioned country

00:30:38.566 --> 00:30:40.299
hasn't yet formed a complete alternative system;

00:30:40.299 --> 00:30:41.299
this is when the impact is highest

00:30:41.299 --> 00:30:43.033
There is a strong incentive

00:30:43.033 --> 00:30:44.433
to make concessions and negotiate,

00:30:44.433 --> 00:30:46.366
but if no agreement is reached at the beginning,

00:30:46.366 --> 00:30:47.333
the longer the sanctions drag on, 

00:30:47.333 --> 00:30:48.833
the less they

00:30:48.833 --> 00:30:50.333
suppress the elites of the sanctioned country

00:30:50.333 --> 00:30:52.100
and the more they suppress the lower classes .

00:30:52.100 --> 00:30:53.799
It becomes difficult to reach an effective agreement,

00:30:53.799 --> 00:30:54.866
leading to a stalemate.

00:30:54.866 --> 00:30:55.966
Academically, this

00:30:55.966 --> 00:30:58.166
creates "sanction fatigue."

00:30:59.133 --> 00:31:00.633
Once sanctions fatigue forms,

00:31:00.633 --> 00:31:02.533
both the sanctioning and sanctioned countries

00:31:02.533 --> 00:31:04.433
will have a group of vested interests,

00:31:04.433 --> 00:31:06.366
making it even more difficult to lift sanctions.

00:31:06.366 --> 00:31:06.933
This

00:31:06.933 --> 00:31:08.833
creates a vicious cycle of sanctions,

00:31:08.833 --> 00:31:10.033
ultimately evolving

00:31:10.033 --> 00:31:12.766
into endless, slow oppression of the lower classes . 

00:31:15.366 --> 00:31:17.133
Actually, I've researched a huge amount of information and data on

00:31:17.133 --> 00:31:18.233
each of the sanctioned countries

00:31:18.233 --> 00:31:20.566
we've discussed today

00:31:20.566 --> 00:31:23.200
However, to maintain a clear structure,

00:31:23.200 --> 00:31:24.033
a manageable length

00:31:24.033 --> 00:31:24.833
and easy-to-understand language

00:31:24.833 --> 00:31:27.033
I've omitted many details and contents.

00:31:27.033 --> 00:31:27.766
Of these countries,

00:31:27.766 --> 00:31:29.766
we've already discussed Russia and Iran;

00:31:29.766 --> 00:31:31.966
I will definitely tackle the rest one by one. 

00:31:31.966 --> 00:31:32.933
That's all for today.

00:31:32.933 --> 00:31:33.899
That's all for today.

